#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.26:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Sīlaṭṭhitivagga"
msgstr "3. Ethics and Duration"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Padesasutta"
msgstr "26. Partly"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.175"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: kaṇḍakīvane → kaṇṭakīvane (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.26:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno āyasmā ca "
"anuruddho sākete viharanti kaṇḍakīvane."
msgstr ""
"At one time the venerables Sāriputta, Mahāmoggallāna, and Anuruddha were "
"staying near Sāketa, in the Thorny Wood."

msgctxt "sn47.26:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca mahāmoggallāno sāyanhasamayaṃ "
"paṭisallānā vuṭṭhitā yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā anuruddhena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta and Mahāmoggallāna came out of "
"retreat, went to Anuruddha, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn47.26:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side. Sāriputta said to Anuruddha:"

#. VAR: sekho, sekho’ti → sekkho sekkhoti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn47.26:1.4"
msgid "“‘sekho, sekho’ti, āvuso anuruddha, vuccati."
msgstr "“Reverend, they speak of this person called ‘a trainee’."

msgctxt "sn47.26:1.5"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, sekho hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How is a trainee defined?”"

msgctxt "sn47.26:1.6"
msgid "“Catunnaṃ kho, āvuso, satipaṭṭhānānaṃ padesaṃ bhāvitattā sekho hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, a trainee is someone who has partly developed the four kinds of "
"mindfulness meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.26:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.26:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.26:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.26:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.26:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.26:2.6"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ padesaṃ bhāvitattā sekho hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"A trainee is someone who has partly developed the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.26:2.7"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
